title: Youth unemployment rate in Saudi Arabia in 2019
summary: Overall Youth unemployment rate has increased over the Year.

Youth unemployment rate is roughly constant from 1999 to 2001, gradually increasing from 2001 to 2005, slightly decreasing from 2005 to 2007, roughly constant from 2007 to 2011, and lastly roughly decreasing from 2011 to 2012.
The most drastic decrease took place within the Year 2006 and 2007.
Maximum Youth unemployment rate, about 33.82 was reported at Year 2006
Minimum Youth unemployment rate about 23.18 was reached at Year 1999
